{
  "texts": [
    "Human raters can then evaluate the indeterminate articles (e.g., articles with ratings between 2 and 4) with greater attentiveness.",
    "By adopting this hybrid approach, the burden on human raters can be reduced significantly, leading to greater time efficiency and increased accuracy, potentially comparable to those of experts.We noticed a surprisingly low agreement score between ChatGPT and the other raters (mean κ = 0.27).",
    "This might point to the AI model's fundamentally different \"thinking\" process, the subjective nature of this process, or simply be due to the selected threshold.",
    "This matter requires further investigations, however, since the LLM is basically an average of its training data -as are most statistical models, this could introduce some levels of objectivity into the field.",
    "It is imperative to state that ChatGPT has been \"aligned\" with human preferences using RLHF."
  ]
}